---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Zone 2 Training Through Loaded Walking"
  description="What does the zone 2 research actually mean for your body? Find out — then walk out the door and do it."
>
<section class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 z-0 bg-topo-pattern opacity-60 [mask-image:linear-gradient(to_bottom,white_20%,transparent_100%)] -mx-50vw"></div>
    
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-stone-900 tracking-tight leading-tight">
        How much should you <span class="text-zone">carry?</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl sm:text-2xl text-stone-500 leading-relaxed bg-white/40 inline-block rounded-lg backdrop-blur-sm pr-4">
        Enter your details. Get your personal zone 2 walking plan — the exact load, pace, and duration for your body. Based on the Pandolf equation, not guesswork.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a
          href={`${base}/load-up`}
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-3.5 bg-zone text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-zone-dark transition-colors text-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md"
        >
          Plan my walk
        </a>
        <a
          href={`${base}/find-your-zone`}
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-3.5 bg-white/80 backdrop-blur text-stone-700 font-semibold rounded-lg border border-stone-300 hover:border-zone hover:text-zone transition-colors text-lg"
        >
          Find my zone 2
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="bg-stone-100 border-y border-stone-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-10">Three tools. No account needed.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

        <a href={`${base}/find-your-zone`} class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200 hover:border-zone/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-3">♡</div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 group-hover:text-zone transition-colors">Find Your Zone 2</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            Calculate your personal zone 2 heart rate range using three research-backed methods. Takes 30 seconds.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/load-up`} class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-zone/30 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-all ring-1 ring-zone/10">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-3">⚖</div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-zone-dark group-hover:text-zone transition-colors">Load Up</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            The reverse calculator. Tell us about you and we'll tell you what to carry and how fast to walk to <em>be</em> in zone 2.
          </p>
          <span class="inline-block mt-3 text-xs font-semibold text-zone bg-zone/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Flagship tool</span>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/session-card`} class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200 hover:border-zone/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="text-3xl mb-3">📋</div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 group-hover:text-zone transition-colors">Session Card</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            Generate a printable walk plan. Take it with you. Leave your phone at home.
          </p>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Walk smarter, not harder</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Zone 2 training — steady, moderate-intensity cardio — is the foundation of cardiovascular health,
          fat metabolism, and longevity. It's what Peter Attia, Andrew Huberman, and exercise physiologist
          Iñigo San Millán have been talking about for years.
        </p>
        <p>
          But most people struggle to stay in zone 2. Jogging pushes you too high. Walking alone isn't enough.
          The sweet spot? <strong>Add weight.</strong> A loaded pack or weighted vest raises your heart rate
          into zone 2 at a comfortable walking pace — no running, no gym, no equipment beyond a rucksack.
        </p>
        <p>
          LoadedZone translates the research into personal numbers. We tell you exactly how much to carry
          and how fast to walk based on your age, weight, fitness level, and terrain. Then we give you a
          printable card so you can leave your phone behind and just walk.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href={`${base}/learn/zone-2-explained`} class="text-zone font-semibold hover:text-zone-dark transition-colors">
          Read the full evidence guide →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-100 border-y border-stone-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Start with what you've got</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            You don't need specialist gear. A rucksack you already own, loaded with books or a bag of
            garden soil, and whatever shoes you walk in today. That's enough to start.
          </p>
          <p>
            No app required. No account. No sign-up. The calculators are free, the session cards are free,
            and the research articles are free. We're not trying to keep you on a screen — we're trying to
            get you out the door.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <a href={`${base}/guides/get-started-free`} class="text-zone font-semibold hover:text-zone-dark transition-colors">
            Read the zero-cost start guide →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>